newsitem.title: CANADA: Thunder Bay vessel clearances - May 21.
newsitem.headline: Thunder Bay vessel clearances - May 21.

text.p: Daily vessel loading/clearances at Thunder Bay, Ontario:
May 16 Ziemia Tarnowksa 18,000 wht Clrd Foreign
May 16 American Mariner 23,000 bly Clrd U.S.A.
May 17 Canadian Ranger 16,000 wht/bly Clrd 3 Rivers
May 17 Federal Saguenay 18,500 wht Clrd Foreign
May 18 G.C. Leitch 25,000 wht Clrd StL
May 19 Canadian Miner 26,000 wht Clrd StL
May 19 American Mariner 13,800 oats Clrd U.S.A.
May 19 Great Laker 18,300 flax Loading Foreign
May 20 El Kef 20,000 wht Waiting Foreign
May 20 Pomorzie Zachodnie 9,000 wht Waiting Forein
May 22 Golden Sky 20,000 wht Due 5/22 Foreign
NOTE: Thunder Bay reopened April 1 when H.M. Griffith cleared.
Note wht=wheat, can=canola, m/wht=milling wheat, dom=domestic
milling wheat, M=meal, P=pellets, O=oil, pea=peas,
lntl=lentils. Ready=preparing to load. MT=metric tonne. Stl
